name: H-E-B
review_text:
Hello
I’ve have shopped at the HEB in Dripping Springs since they have opened a few years ago.   I have always been treated very well here with the exception of a certain cashier named Diana.   I have had the extreme displeasure of having Diana as my cashier three times.   Each time she has been nothing but extremely rude , curt , and disrespectful to me and my family.    I have never been treated so poorly at any HEB.   Each time this has happened, I have respectfully communicated the issues with HEB management , they seem baffled and claim they have will end the problem.   Seems like management has no problem with Diana and her style of being rude to people.    Diana should flip burgers instead of working with customers.  I will take my business elsewhere.   I can afford it.
owner_answer: Hi, Chris. We value hearing from our customers to know what we could be doing better. If you'd like to follow up with us, please call us at 1-800-432-3113 from 8 am to 5 pm (Monday - Friday) to speak with a Partner.

name: H-E-B
review_text: The last bagger I encountered threw my produce (apples, potatoes, onions) into random bags when they slipped out of the conveyor belt - I only noticed when I saw an empty produce bag with onion skins shoved to the side. I asked her can I have that (to show her manager) and she THREW it at me. Management needs to get after the younger cashiers and baggers (this coming from a 22 year old with manners) - oh yeah, and expect side eyes, being on their phone while at cashier, and overstuffing the bags. Awful customer service.
owner_answer: We are concerned about what you experienced in-store and want to follow up with you. Please call us at your earliest convenience at 1-800-432-3113. Our Partners will be available Monday – Friday from 8 a.m. to 5 p.m. CST to help look into this matter.

name: H-E-B
review_text:
its HEB, but this location is just okay! Managers just sit around, lines, super slow, as busy as this HEB is, you think they would be fully staffed. This HEB really needs help. Poorly managed store. Called the store and the girl at the CS desk suggested I come early in the AM, when the typical American is working. Really helpful. Thanks.

EDIT: wow this HEB is really really bad.
owner_answer: Thank you for letting us know what you experienced, Scott. Knowing what we can be doing better helps us improve. If you’d like to discuss this further, please give us a call at 1-800-432-3113 from 8 a.m. to 5 p.m. CST.

name: H-E-B
review_text: Because of your managers and the cashier named Diana , I will now drive to Wimberley Texas to do my grocery shopping.    I will go to brookshire brothers.   I will gladly drive the 30 extra minutes to avoid rude cashiers like Diana , whom has now zero Skills in being friendly and lazy managers that just observe and laugh and giggle instead of getting their hands dirty and help the staff.
owner_answer: Hello Ryan and thanks for writing to us. We’re sorry to see this and would like to follow up with you. At your convenience, please give us a call at 1-800-432-3113 from 8 a.m. to 5 p.m. CST and one of our Partners will be able to help.

name: H-E-B
review_text: They have these store coupons and they never work at check out. Then I get adtide from the cashiers. You dont like working there leave otherwise learn what then term customer service means. Not to mention the inability to get help finding things. HEB has lost their way Location

name: H-E-B
review_text: This latest revelation is a deal-killer. The store was overrun with shoppers, no masks, all their kids running wild up and down the crowded aisles. While the management may simply not be prepared to regulate the shoppers, they could regulate their own practices during this horrific time. None of the checkers had masks or gloves. Social distancing was unheard of. No sanitizer that was readily available for customers' hands. It was a cesspool of defiance regarding safe practices. Thank goodness it's only a 30-minute drive into Austin. Just called Sprouts and verified that all checkers and shelf stockers are wearing the basics of masks and gloves. Oh, yes, they are. Distancing is strictly enforced. Funny what 20 miles can do. I'll be happy to keep Austin weird.

name: H-E-B
review_text: Worst HEB EVER. I GO in with list of 8 normal things and they are out of 4 of them. They have stocked with overkill on HEB products and done away with name brands. Produce is AWFUL. They say everything will be great when Curbside shopping comes in. WHAT A JOKE! There is not one person I know that wants one of the workers picking out their groceries. Can not wait until a different grocery store is built in Dripping Springs. Maybe then and ONLY then, this store will get their act together.

name: H-E-B
review_text: This store is nasty,cluttered,does not have room for qll the products you are trying to sell. You can't find what you want,Sorry but this store needs a remotel and makeover. The prices are outrageous, milk is $1.78 at our HEB in Mont Belvieu, you want $2.98-$3.98. Your sushi bar had no product at 630pm, only 5-6 items. SAD

name: H-E-B
review_text:
It was annoying. Been waiting... For days!  To pick up an RX. Kept being told: We're waiting for call back from your Dr to refill... However, they had sent their request to a  Dr that retired last year. We have given the pharmacy the new RX and new Dr's contact info on several occasions. But, HEB pharmacy now says they have no info or RX from our current Dr. So here we go again. Have to get a new RX.... Again!  So, perhaps you can feel our frustration. Thank you!
2

name: H-E-B
review_text: This is by far the worst HEB in the Hill Country area. Marble Falls (new store) is the best one. Next would be Bulverde. Then I would have to say Fredericksburg. The HEB in Dripping Springs is garbage.

name: H-E-B
review_text: FYI...I live in Wimberley but do most of my bulk shopping at the Dripping location.  Never had a problem before, but on Sunday  I bought some Wonton wrappers to make home made egg rolls.  Tried to use them last night, and when I opened the package, they were rancid!  The date said 5/20/17.  Nevertheless, they were rancid.  Buyer beware.

name: H-E-B
review_text: Constantly discontinuing products I purchase weekly.  Things I can buy at other HEB stores,  I'm told the dripping springs store will no longer carry.  This happens over n over again. I'll drive the extra 10 miles to shop elsewhere.  Where my input matters.

name: H-E-B
review_text: There is nothing wrong with the store it's self. Cashier's are friendly. Pickers are a little rude sometimes. But it is always packed with the rudest, try to run over people. Even the parking lot. It is not a pleasant experience. Been going to Wimberly more it's a whole different experience.

name: H-E-B
review_text:
1st keep in mind I love the Dripping Springs HEB store, very nice people friendly and helpful to customers but as they say there is always one bad apple in the bunch.
The store had opened at 6am but it was already 7:30 when I was there and the overnight stock staff were still working and the isles were cram packed with cases of product and lots of empty boxes (trash) making it difficult to navigate almost every isle in the store.  One a-hole guy, when I came up to him and patiently waited for him to move his trash so I could get through looked up at me and shook his head with disgust that he had to clear the isle.  To me that is rude and he really doesn't realize that myself and other shoppers (in the grand scheme of things) pays his salary!  Where would he be without the customers??
HEB management maybe should hold a training session for these people and let them know that they should show courtesy to the customers as much as the checkers and other staff do..  Just a hint.
To all the others (not the a-hole guy) you do a fantastic job and you were all champions during the pandemic by coming to work each day and serving us.  Thank you so much
owner_answer: Thank you for letting us know what you experienced, knowing what we can be doing better helps us improve, Bob. Please know your feedback will be shared with the store, but if you’d like to discuss this further, please call us Monday- Friday at 1-800-432-3113 from 8 a.m. to 5 p.m. CST to speak with a Partner.

name: H-E-B
review_text: I am a frequent shopper and over the last several visits I've been disappointed in the availability of items (empty shelves) and the facing of stocked items. I know that due to the pandemic, stores are not well stocked for reasons beyond their control, but I've been to other HEBs in the area and I find they are far better stocked. And, what is on their shelves is up front where shoppers can reach and get to items. Many times I've had to get on my knees to reach items on the lower shelf that are way in the back. As many times I've had to reach up on the very top shelf, where extra items are, because the item's shelf is empty. Just today, I helped a customer who couldn't reach that top shelf. Frustrated, and shopping in Wimberley or Austin where I can find and access everything I need, even if further away.
owner_answer: We’re sorry to see this and would like to follow up with you. At your convenience, please give us a call at 1-800-432-3113 from 8 a.m. to 5 p.m. CST and one of our Partners will be able to help.

name: H-E-B
review_text: Love almost all the employees nothing ever wrong with them, however I do have some honest issues. I purchased beer from this HEB that had gone bad on the shelf I got bad food poisoning from it as well and while I do like most of the employees I'm afraid one or two of the cashiers on occasion where rude. Now I don't know if they work there anymore but at the time I had one older woman who made rude comments to me and another who chatted up a storm with the person in front of me while they moved their 40 item cart through the  15 limit item checkout with a few carts behind as well.

name: H-E-B
review_text: I love HEB but this one is frequently out of stock on items, or doesn't carry them. The flower department is limited but the bakery department is good. We order mini wedding cakes here and they are always good. Hopefully they will remodel this one and add more relevant stuff.

name: H-E-B
review_text: This HEB does not enforce wearing mask while in the store regardless of the huge sign stating that all are required to mask while in the store. At this point you are either part of the solution or you are contributing to the problem. This store is flirting with complacency on this issue.

name: H-E-B
review_text: I’ve lived here for 11 years and I think it’s a crying shame that this town, given avg population income, gets an HEB of this scale.  It’s embarrassing, or should be for HEB HQ. I know for a fact this store grosses more than $1M per week and we have this crummy little store. Product availability is scarce and always in need of stocking. Go check out he HEB in Buda or Kyle or BeeCave for that matter..makes this store look like red-headed step child.  I would rather travel 30mi one way than shop here and often do. Hope this review gets corporate off their comfortable bun$ and expand this store and give us the store we deserve!

name: H-E-B
review_text: Good HEB but can not stand the staff at times. Some are just plain rude. I'm very surprised at how they even get hired in the first place. Well I meet this one girl, Victoria C. Super rude, has no manners whatsoever! I ask "Hey, how are you?" Looks right at me, knows I'm talking to her then just gives me a dirty look. I've never met this person in my life.. so what's her problem? Then as she's bagging my groceries she is literally throwing them down and seriously broke 5 of my eggs and smashed my crackers. I'd rather bag my groceries any ways. Should of just told her to leave my sh*t alone. Next time I guess I'll have to speak up. Hope she gets that stick out of her butt and gets a better attitude.

name: H-E-B
review_text:
If you like HEB branded product then this is the place for you.  If you want the brands you grew up on and are familiar with then you will find yourself very frustrated visiting this HEB store.  Hopefully HEB realizes not everyone wants the cheapest products made and can cater their brands to the areas demographic a little better.  I know they can do it by the types of product sold now so zeroing in on the brands and quality of products sold should be their next step.

Your speed bumps are ridiculous.

name: H-E-B
review_text: We bought some Red Diamond Tea and went to bring it back and warn them that it had a pin hole in it.  The Girl in Customer Service was so RUDE!!!!! She treated my husband as if he done it and also refused to trade it OUT!!!! SO Check your Tea.... When we went to the 2nd one we bought it was the SAME 🤦‍♀️😳

name: H-E-B
review_text: I called 7 different HEB's and this location was the only one with a opening for my daughter's wedding date. The florist here has not been very pleasant to deal with, she doesn't return phone calls or emails. She says one thing and it's another. I have sent Veronica at least 10 emails and she's still not got things together. My daughter's wedding date is October 20th and I still don't have flowers. Weddings are so stressful, especially when you are working with someone who says one thing and does another. Now I'm stuck with no Fresh Flowers for our only daughter's wedding. I will never return to this store again. I  was just informed that she wants a 320 dollar Delivery fee fo a Venue that's only 15 miles away. Needless to say I still don't have a florist  for my daughter's wedding.

name: H-E-B
review_text: I am very disapointed at the customer service as of late. For the past several months I have had to bag my groceries everytime. This evening after working all day and driving an hour home from work, I had to stop and do so some shopping. It takes so much more time when I have to bag the groceries. Especially when I am buying for a family with 3 teenagers. I am seriously considering going back to the Bee Caves HEB from now on. They were extremely busy and only had 2 people bagging. Maybe that is just something grocery stores don't offer anymore.....

name: H-E-B
review_text:
I will give you the good news first, I have been delighted to have HEB here inDripping Springs. In the last month to six weeks I have seen a steady decline in the produce offered. It was appaling when I went yesterday 10/6/15. there were short supplies, old and wrinkled veggies, chaos trying to reah what I wanted. Every week when I go I buy apples, usually six and a different variety each week but for the last four weeks at least about half of my apples are bad when I cut into them. They are not cheap and I consider them expensive deer food.  You stopped carrying the Taylor Farms bag salads and put in your own and they are nowhere near as good. I thought I should let you know and also let you know that there are many others unhappy. We always bragged on our HEB and not much to brag about now. Another thing I have noticed that for well over two months I cannot get the party size Fritos, have to go to Walmart for those, I won't stop coming there but I am disappointed.

hank you, Helen G.

name: H-E-B
review_text:
Big store, small town attitude. When my favorite brand was being discontinued I asked the manager if they would please keep it on the shelf for me. They did! That's not common in this day and age for big stores.
Update,  they lied. Not happy!
